			<a class="bold" name="18">I used to have an account. Do I have to sign up again to use 6FigureJobs?</a><br>
			<p>No. Just log into you account and you’ll have the option to choose a recruitment plan to reactivate your account. If you do not remember your login credentials, then call us at 800.605.5154 or live chat so we can quickly assist you.&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="##top">top</a></p>

			<a class="bold" name="19">I have a multiple user recruitment package. How do I set up additional users?</a><br>
			<p>Login to your Dashboard. Under your “Recruitment Plan” section, there is an “Assign Users” link that take you to the page where you manage and add your user licenses.&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="##top">top</a></p>

			<a class="bold" name="20">How do I change my password?</a><br>
			<p>Login to your Dashboard. Under your “Recruitment Plan” section, there is an “Assign Users” link that take you to the page where you manage your user licenses. Click on the user license you wish to modify.&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="##top">top</a></p>

			<a class="bold" name="21">When I post a job are applicants directed to apply through my company website or do they email me their application?</a><br>
			<p>
				You have a few options when posting a job on 6FigureJobs.<br><br>
				A) You can specify a Job URL, which redirects the job seeker to apply on your career (or ATS) site.
				<br><br>
				OR
				<br><br>
				B) You can disclose the contact information of the recruiter/hiring manager (name and/or email) who receives the job applications, to encourage the candidate to email his/her application directly through his/her own personal email account.
				<br><br>
				OR
				<br><br>
				C) You can choose NOT to disclose the contact information of the recruiter/hiring manager, so that the candidate applies through our Job Application System. When a candidate clicks on the Apply to Job button, we will send a Job Notification Email to the recruiter/hiring manager associated with your account. He/she receives a nicely packaged email with the candidate's profile snapshot, contact information and attached resume. You also have access to a Job Applications folder when you log into the site, where we keep a record of ALL the job applications for that job.
				&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="##top">top</a>
			</p>

			<a class="bold" name="22">Do the professionals (job seekers) on 6FigureJobs have to pay to search and apply to jobs?</a><br>
			<p>No. Since 1999 6FigureJobs has always given job seekers FREE membership to search and apply. We want active and passive seekers to utilize 6FigureJobs as a tool to keep their eyes and ears open for new opportunities. This also allows more job seekers to stay engaged in our community. A common problem with premium pay sites.&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="##top">top</a></p>

			<a class="bold" name="23">My company has a military/veteran hiring initiative. Is it easy to search for military veterans?</a><br>
			<p>Yes. We have a search filter just for that!&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="##top">top</a></p>

			<a class="bold" name="24">Do all jobs have to be six-figure in salary?</a><br>
			<p>Yes. Our name says it all. It’s a requirement that differentiates us. We receive inquiries from companies about sales opportunities. Sales positions must also offer the professional the opportunity to make $100K+ in “total compensation.” If a position offers a base below $100K, but allows the professional to exceed $100K through bonus, stock, or commission plans - then we also accept these unique job opportunities onto our board.&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="##top">top</a></p>

			<a class="bold" name="25">Can I add multiple user search licenses to my recruitment plan?</a><br>
			<p>Yes. Your account manager can easily accommodate you. See our pricing page for details.&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="##top">top</a></p>
			
			<a class="bold" name="26">What exactly do you mean by “pre-screened” candidates?</a><br>
			<p>We are a free career site for job seekers. This means that every day we receive a lot of membership registrations from all sorts of job seekers. Because we are free, we do not accept everyone. Six-figure jobs for senior-level and executive professionals is our niche. Recruiters use 6FigureJobs to specifically target senior-level and executive professionals. It is important for us to review and accept/reject registrations to maintain a quality and relevant community. We look closely at each job seeker who registers to ensure they have a legitimate profile, work experience, resume and six-figure compensation history.&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="##top">top</a></p>

			<a class="bold" name="27">Do you let job seekers into your community if they do not make $100K+?</a><br>
			<p>After reviewing a job seeker’s membership application, we accept or reject them based on their complete profile and their compensation history. We often accept job seekers into our community if they say they make $70K to $99K in salary. We also take into account their current situation. Due to the poor economy, we understand that professionals are unemployed or working at a lower salary than they did before.&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="##top">top</a></p>
